WEBVTT

00:01.500 --> 00:02.990
MY NAME IS ALEX PARRISH.

00:03.000 --> 00:04.536
PROTECTING OUR COUNTRY
HAD ALWAYS BEEN MY DREAM,

00:04.540 --> 00:06.826
BUT MY LIFE
TOOK A VERY DRASTIC TURN.

00:06.830 --> 00:09.298
IT ALL STARTED NINE MONTHS AGO
ON MY WAY TO THE FBI ACADEMY.

00:09.300 --> 00:13.179
WE'RE COMMI'I'I'ING TO LIFE
AS ONE AGENT, ONE PERSON.

00:13.180 --> 00:14.215
Simon:
I HAVE NOTHING TO HIDE.

00:14.220 --> 00:15.756
GOOD, THEN I HAVE
NOTHING TO FIND

00:15.760 --> 00:17.079
WHEN THE U.A.W.C.
E-MAILS ME BACK.

00:17.090 --> 00:19.058
HI, MA.
I JOINED THE FBI.

00:19.060 --> 00:20.095
YOU'RE ON PROBATION.

00:20.100 --> 00:22.182
IF YOU FAIL OUT OF HERE,
YOU ARE OUT.

00:22.190 --> 00:24.181
I NEVER THOUGHT
BEFORE I'D SAVE OUR COUNTRY,

00:24.190 --> 00:25.726
I'D HAVE TO SAVE MYSELF.

00:25.730 --> 00:27.300
YOU COULD HAVE RIGGED THE BOMB
TO BLOW REMOTELY.

00:27.310 --> 00:29.608
THE BOMBS -- SEVEN --

00:29.610 --> 00:33.398
THEY HAD TO HAVE BEEN TRIGGERED
WITHIN A TWO-BLOCK RADIUS.

00:33.410 --> 00:35.901
YOU'RE GONNA TELL ME HOW THIS
WIRE FROM YOUR FAMILY BUSINESS

00:35.910 --> 00:37.446
ENDED UP AS A PART
OF THOSE BOMBS.

00:37.450 --> 00:39.281
Clayton: PARRISH HAS TAKEN
ANOTHER HOSTAGE.

00:39.290 --> 00:40.609
FROM HERE ON OUT,
IT'S SHOOT TO KILL.

00:40.620 --> 00:42.417
I NEED TO FIND THE TRUTH.

00:42.420 --> 00:45.912
WHAT I WANT TO KNOW IS,
WHO IS ALEX PARRISH?

00:45.920 --> 00:49.504
THEY SAY SHE'S AN AMERICAN.

00:49.510 --> 00:54.538
BUT WHAT KIND OF AMERICAN
MURDERS 130 INNOCENT PEOPLE?

00:54.550 --> 00:58.338
WHAT KIND OF AMERICAN
HATES THIS COUNTRY SO MUCH

00:58.340 --> 01:01.844
THAT THEY INFILTRATE THE FBI
TO DESTROY US?

01:05.230 --> 01:08.848
I DON'T KNOW WHERE
SHE WAS BORN -- INDIA? EGYPT?

01:08.850 --> 01:10.989
BUT IT'S TIME TO CATCH HER

01:10.990 --> 01:13.527
AND TEACH HER WHAT
THIS COUNTRY'S REALLY ABOUT.

01:15.740 --> 01:17.640
YOU'VE BEEN PACING
FOR OVER AN HOUR.

01:17.650 --> 01:19.459
THEY'RE GOING TO CATCH YOU,
ALEX.

01:19.460 --> 01:21.781
THE E.A.D. IS A PERSONAL FRIEND.
HE WON'T --

01:21.790 --> 01:22.996
WOULD YOU PLEASE
STOP TALKING?

01:23.000 --> 01:24.740
-WHY DID YOU DO IT?
-I DIDN'T.

01:24.750 --> 01:26.069
SO TURN YOURSELF IN.

01:26.080 --> 01:28.401
TO WHO? THE BUREAU, WHERE
SOMEONE'S TRYING TO FRAME ME?

01:28.410 --> 01:29.911
YOU NEED TO
TURN YOURSELF IN, SHELBY.

01:29.920 --> 01:31.968
THE ONLY REAL PIECE OF EVIDENCE
POINTS TO YOU.

01:31.970 --> 01:33.619
WHAT, YOU MEAN THE WIRE
THAT YOU FOUND

01:33.630 --> 01:35.200
IN THE APARTMENT
NEXT TO YOURS?

01:35.210 --> 01:36.586
THAT COULD POINT
TO ANYONE.

01:36.590 --> 01:39.673
IT'S MILITARY ORIGIN,
SO THAT'S RYAN

01:39.680 --> 01:42.922
OR THE -- THE FRIENDS
THAT SIMON MADE IN GAZA

01:42.930 --> 01:45.307
OR THE CARTELS
THAT VASQUEZ DEALT WITH

01:45.310 --> 01:46.550
AS A COP IN TEXAS.

01:46.560 --> 01:47.970
EVEN CALEB COULD HAVE
GOTI'EN HIS HANDS ON IT

01:47.980 --> 01:49.186
THROUGH HIS FAMILY.

01:49.190 --> 01:51.272
AND IF YOU REALLY ARE
INNOCENT,

01:51.280 --> 01:53.931
YOU SHOULD WORRY ABOUT
HOW GUILTY YOU LOOK RIGHT NOW,

01:53.940 --> 01:56.818
BECAUSE AN INNOCENT PERSON
DOES NOT TAKE SOMEONE HOSTAGE.

01:56.820 --> 01:58.685
EVEN AN INNOCENT PERSON
NEEDS LEVERAGE,

01:58.690 --> 02:00.237
AND YOU'RE MINE.

02:00.240 --> 02:01.730
SO YOU BETTER
GET COMFORTABLE

02:01.740 --> 02:03.037
BECAUSE WE MIGHT BE HERE
FOR A WHILE.

02:04.330 --> 02:05.399
OH, OH, OH, OH

02:05.410 --> 02:07.787
OH, OH, OH, OH, OH

02:07.790 --> 02:08.859
ALL RIGHT, SHOW ME SOMETHING,
PEOPLE.

02:08.870 --> 02:10.747
I KNOW YOU'RE TIRED.

02:10.750 --> 02:12.001
HA!
MY DADDY SAYS
THAT LIFE COMES AT YOU FAST

02:12.010 --> 02:14.126
[ BUZZING ]
WE ALL LIKE BLADES OF GRASS

02:14.130 --> 02:15.870
WE COME TO PRIME
NIMAH!

02:15.880 --> 02:18.041
AND IN TIME,
WE JUST WITHER AWAY
IT'S YOUR MORNING!

02:18.050 --> 02:19.847
YOU WERE SUPPOSED TO BE AT P.T.
AN HOUR AGO!

02:19.850 --> 02:22.466
I'M SORRY. I STAYED UP ALL NIGHT
STUDYING WHAT I MISSED.

02:22.470 --> 02:23.926
YOU SAID YOU'D STEP IT UP.

02:23.930 --> 02:25.886
IF YOU CAN'T,
THIS IS NEVER GONNA WORK.

02:25.890 --> 02:28.757
I KNOW YOU'VE BEEN WORKING HARD.
I KNOW YOU'RE HOMESICK.

02:28.760 --> 02:30.978
MOM, THAT'S ENOUGH.
I KNOW YOU DON'T WANT ME HERE.

02:30.980 --> 02:32.891
MOM: Well, what do you mean
you know what I'm going to say?

02:32.900 --> 02:34.640
BECAUSE WE HAVE THE SAME FIGHT
EVERY SINGLE --
Who's fault is that?

02:34.650 --> 02:36.106
[ GRUNTS ]

02:36.110 --> 02:37.975
BUT IF YOU THINK
THIS IS PRESSURE,

02:37.980 --> 02:40.369
WAIT UNTIL
YOU'RE OUT IN THE FIELD.

02:40.370 --> 02:41.735
LOOK, IF YOU'RE JUST
GONNA YELL, THEN --
You shouldn't have enrolled
there behind my back!

02:41.740 --> 02:43.617
SCREAM

02:43.620 --> 02:45.326
WELL, I WAS TOO YOUNG
TO UNDERSTAND WHAT IT MEANS

02:45.330 --> 02:46.979
Ryan: O'CONNOR KNOWS
THAT I'M ON TO HIM.

02:46.990 --> 02:48.617
AND HE CAN PUT THE SCREWS TO ME
ALL HE WANTS,

02:48.620 --> 02:50.167
BUT HE'S UP TO SOMETHING
WITH ALEX, TOO.

02:50.170 --> 02:51.660
I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO DO.

02:51.670 --> 02:53.240
RIGHT NOW,
YOU DO NOTHING.

02:53.250 --> 02:54.911
HE ALREADY PUT YOU
ON PROBATION.

02:54.920 --> 02:56.990
IF HE REALLY THINKS ALEX IS SOME
SORT OF THREAT TO THE BUREAU,

02:57.000 --> 02:58.706
I'LL FIND OUT WHY.

02:58.710 --> 03:00.553
NOW I WISH I COULD
FREEZE THE TIME AT 17

03:00.560 --> 03:02.130
[ GRUNTING ]

03:02.140 --> 03:05.678
OH, OH, OH, OH, OH

03:05.680 --> 03:07.056
SIMON...

03:07.060 --> 03:09.176
WHERE DID YOU LEARN
TO FIGHT LIKE THAT?

03:09.180 --> 03:10.647
HEBREW SCHOOL.

03:10.650 --> 03:12.766
OH, OH, OH, OH, OH

03:12.770 --> 03:14.101
OH, OH, OH, OH, OH

03:14.110 --> 03:15.566
17
Elias: BAD TIME?

03:15.570 --> 03:16.935
NOW I WISH I COULD
FREEZE THE TIME AT 17

03:16.940 --> 03:18.805
NOPE.
JUST SKYPING WITH MAX.

03:18.810 --> 03:20.619
YOUR BOYFRIEND?

03:20.620 --> 03:22.770
I'D LOVE TO MEET HIM.
GET HIM BACK SO I CAN SAY HI.

03:22.780 --> 03:24.611
OH, WELL,
HE, UH -- HE'S --

03:24.620 --> 03:26.861
FICTIONAL?
THAT'S WHAT I THINK, ANYWAY.

03:26.870 --> 03:29.020
THEY KEEP YOU GROUNDED

03:29.030 --> 03:30.873
Liam:
20 SECONDS, THEN YOU'RE DONE.

03:30.880 --> 03:32.586
WITH GOOD ADVICE

03:32.590 --> 03:34.740
Shelby:
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

03:34.750 --> 03:36.991
I THOUGHT YOU GAVE UP
THIS GHOST.

03:37.000 --> 03:39.503
WELL,
THERE'S NO Xboxes AROUND.

03:39.510 --> 03:42.638
AND I NEED TO DO SOMETHING
WITH MY HANDS.

03:42.640 --> 03:45.336
UNLESS YOU GOT
ANY BE'I'I'ER IDEAS.

03:45.340 --> 03:47.638
WHAT IF A FIELD COUNSELOR
SEES YOU?

03:47.640 --> 03:49.551
THEN MY MAN TOM AT
THE FRONT DESK WILL WARN ME.

03:49.560 --> 03:51.107
HEY, TOM.

03:51.110 --> 03:52.839
WE'VE GOT A SYSTEM.
YOU COULD GET KICKED OUT.

03:52.850 --> 03:54.397
HEY, BUNS AND AMMO,

03:54.400 --> 03:56.891
I GOT IT UNDER CONTROL,
ALL RIGHT?

03:56.900 --> 04:00.484
I WAS TOO YOUNG TO UNDERSTAND
WHAT IT MEANS

04:00.490 --> 04:03.118
TIME.
ALL RIGHT, HIT THE SHOWERS.

04:03.120 --> 04:04.690
CLASS IN 10 MINUTES.

04:04.700 --> 04:06.349
YOU KNOW WHAT I COULD GO FOR
RIGHT ABOUT NOW?

04:06.360 --> 04:07.440
A PEPPERONI PIZZA.

04:07.450 --> 04:09.156
OH, YES.

04:09.160 --> 04:11.321
THAT WAS THE FIRST THING
I ATE AFTER I GOT BACK
FROM EACH DEPLOYMENT --

04:11.330 --> 04:14.709
A PEPPERONI PIZZA
AND A BEER.

04:14.710 --> 04:15.529
OR SIX.

04:15.540 --> 04:17.076
[ LAUGHS ]

04:17.080 --> 04:19.753
THE FIRST THING I ATE
AFTER 10 YEARS IN MUMBAI --

04:19.760 --> 04:22.001
MMM, A CHEESEBURGER.

04:22.010 --> 04:23.637
YOU KNOW, A GUY TOLD ME ABOUT
A DINER ABOUT A MILE FROM HERE.

04:23.640 --> 04:25.710
I BET YOU THEY SERVE
A MEAN CHEESEBURGER.

04:25.720 --> 04:27.506
EXCEPT WE CAN'T
LEAVE CAMPUS YET.

04:27.510 --> 04:29.728
OR DID YOU FORGET ABOUT
THAT LITTLE RULE?

04:29.730 --> 04:31.686
[ SIGHS ]
A GUY CAN DREAM, CAN'T HE?

04:31.690 --> 04:33.260
I HOPE SO.

04:33.270 --> 04:34.726
THAT'S ABOUT
ALL WE CAN DO THESE DAYS.

04:34.730 --> 04:37.938
YOU DO KNOW YOUR COLOGNE ARRIVES
12 SECONDS BEFORE YOU?

04:37.940 --> 04:39.396
WELL,
I DON'T WEAR COLOGNE.

04:39.400 --> 04:42.449
SO YOU CLEARLY RESPOND TO ME
ON A CELLULAR LEVEL.

04:42.450 --> 04:44.736
DOES THE FBI PROCESS
RESTRAINING ORDERS?

04:44.740 --> 04:46.059
YOU KNOW, IT'S MY JOB

04:46.070 --> 04:48.356
TO ANALYZE EACH NAT'S
STRENGTHS AND WEAKNESSES,

04:48.360 --> 04:50.499
AND I THINK I JUST
FOUND YOURS.
HM?

04:50.500 --> 04:51.489
IT'S ME.

04:51.500 --> 04:52.785
Field Counselor: HAAS.

04:52.790 --> 04:54.576
YES, SIR?

04:54.580 --> 04:56.707
DIDN'T I ALREADY WARN YOU ABOUT
OPERATING A GUN ON CAMPUS?

04:56.710 --> 04:57.950
YES, SIR.

04:57.960 --> 05:00.588
THEN WHY DO I HEAR YOU'RE
AT THE RANGE TWICE A DAY?

05:00.590 --> 05:03.411
THIS IS YOUR SECOND WARNING.
THERE WON'T BE A THIRD.

05:06.130 --> 05:07.119
YOU TOLD THEM?

05:07.130 --> 05:08.506
NO, I DIDN'T TELL ANYONE.

05:08.510 --> 05:09.977
OH, SO TOM DECIDED
TO RAT ME OUT

05:09.980 --> 05:11.766
AFTER FIVE DAYS
OF LETTING ME IN, NO PROBLEM?

05:11.770 --> 05:13.340
IF THAT'S THE WAY YOU WANT
TO PLAY IT, HEIGL,

05:13.350 --> 05:14.886
YOU BETTER WATCH
YOUR BACK.

05:14.890 --> 05:17.051
NEXT TIME, YOU'RE NOT GONNA
SMELL ME COMING.

05:19.020 --> 05:21.773
15 WEEKS,
AND THEN WE'RE ALL FREE.

05:21.780 --> 05:23.270
IF WE ALL MAKE IT.

05:24.110 --> 05:26.431
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATES ]

05:29.620 --> 05:32.282
Miranda: WELL,
AREN'T YOU A SORRY BUNCH?

05:32.290 --> 05:35.441
USUALLY IT TAKES RECRUITS
MONTHS TO LOOK THIS EXHAUSTED.

05:35.450 --> 05:37.748
YOU MUST BE
DOING SOMETHING RIGHT.

05:37.750 --> 05:40.958
WHICH IS WHY YOU'RE GETTING
THE NIGHT OFF...

05:40.960 --> 05:42.006
WOW!

05:42.010 --> 05:44.331
...OUTSIDE OF THE ACADEMY.

05:44.340 --> 05:46.581
WELL, NOT EXACTLY YOU.

05:46.590 --> 05:49.218
THIS WEEK'S EXERCISE
IS ABOUT GOING UNDERCOVER.

05:49.220 --> 05:52.963
EACH OF YOU WILL BUILD A PERSONA
OF A WHITE-COLLAR EMPLOYEE

05:52.970 --> 05:54.926
AT A FORTUNE 500 COMPANY.

05:54.930 --> 05:57.888
NOW, I KNOW THIS IS NOT AS SEXY
AS THE MOB.

05:57.890 --> 06:01.974
BUT IN TODAY'S STATE OF AFFAIRS,
IT IS THE MOST LIKELY SCENARIO.

06:01.980 --> 06:03.777
THOSE OF YOU WHO EXCEL

06:03.780 --> 06:06.772
WILL GET TO TRY OUT
YOUR PERSONAS TONIGHT

06:06.780 --> 06:09.692
IN A REAL-LIFE SETTING
TO SEE IF THEY HOLD.

06:09.700 --> 06:12.112
AGENT O'CONNOR?

06:12.120 --> 06:15.533
IN EVERYDAY LIFE,
YOU KNOW WHO YOU ARE --

06:15.540 --> 06:18.828
THE PLACE YOU LIVE, YOUR CAREER,
YOUR RELIGION,

06:18.830 --> 06:20.627
HOW YOU WERE RAISED.

06:20.630 --> 06:22.336
THERE'S CERTAIN THINGS
YOU CAN CHANGE,

06:22.340 --> 06:25.992
BUT THE CAKE, AS THEY SAY,
IS BAKED.

06:26.000 --> 06:28.753
UNDERCOVER, YOU GET A CHANCE
TO START OVER.

06:28.760 --> 06:30.307
CONTROL HOW PEOPLE SEE YOU.

06:30.310 --> 06:33.677
CAN YOU CREATE A PERSON SO REAL

06:33.680 --> 06:36.558
THAT YOU CONVINCE THE WORLD
YOU ARE WHO YOU SAY YOU ARE?

06:38.310 --> 06:40.687
CAN YOU DISAPPEAR?

06:40.690 --> 06:42.772
Alex:
RYAN? WHERE ARE YOU?

06:42.780 --> 06:44.145
I'M HERE WITH SIMON.

06:44.150 --> 06:45.936
THANK GOD YOU ANSWERED
SHELBY'S PHONE.

06:45.940 --> 06:47.567
WHAT IS IT?
DID SOMETHING HAPPEN?

06:47.570 --> 06:49.014
An order just came down.

06:49.020 --> 06:50.692
FROM NOW ON, THEY'RE NOT TRYING
TO TAKE YOU IN.

06:50.700 --> 06:51.985
IT'S SHOOT ON SIGHT.

06:53.490 --> 06:56.072
THEY'VE SENTENCED ME
TO DEATH.

06:56.080 --> 06:57.320
WE'RE GONNA FIND THE PERSON
WHO DID THIS.

06:57.330 --> 06:58.228
I promise you that.

06:58.240 --> 06:59.662
HOW?

06:59.670 --> 07:01.035
NO ONE'S LOOKING BUT ME.

07:01.040 --> 07:02.337
ALEX --

07:02.340 --> 07:03.989
LOOK,
THEY'RE GETTING DESPERATE.

07:04.000 --> 07:04.876
OKAY, THAT'S ALL THIS IS.

07:04.880 --> 07:06.666
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

07:06.670 --> 07:08.877
[ SNIFFLES ]
THESE PEOPLE KNOW ME.

07:08.880 --> 07:10.802
I'M NO DIFFERENT THAN I WAS
TWO DAYS AGO.

07:10.810 --> 07:13.847
FOR THE MOMENT, STAY INDOORS.
STAY OFF THE RADAR.

07:13.850 --> 07:15.249
WHAT IF I DON'T MAKE IT?

07:15.260 --> 07:16.807
Look, don't say that,
all right?

07:16.810 --> 07:19.938
ALEX, DON'T LOSE HOPE, OKAY?
ALEX?

07:19.940 --> 07:20.816
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]
ALEX?

07:23.690 --> 07:25.601
SHE HUNG UP.
LOOK, WE HAVE TO MOVE FAST.

07:25.610 --> 07:27.225
THERE'S GOT TO BE SOMETHING
WE CAN DO FROM HERE.

07:27.230 --> 07:29.221
OKAY, SHELBY SAID THAT THE BOMBS
HAD TO HAVE BEEN TRIGGERED

07:29.230 --> 07:30.276
WITHIN A TWO-BLOCK RADIUS,
RIGHT?

07:30.280 --> 07:32.020
SO WHOEVER
CARRIED OUT THE ATTACK

07:32.030 --> 07:33.861
NEEDED A REASON
TO BE NEAR GRAND CENTRAL.

07:33.870 --> 07:34.859
IF WE FIND A LIST

07:34.870 --> 07:36.440
OF FBI PERSONNEL
ON DUTY YESTERDAY...

07:36.450 --> 07:37.860
THE BOMBER'S MOST LIKELY
ON THAT LIST.

07:37.870 --> 07:40.077
LET ME SEND AN E-MAIL.
I'LL TRACK IT DOWN.

07:43.580 --> 07:45.628
[ CELLPHONE THUDS ]

07:45.630 --> 07:47.370
YOU LOOK WORRIED.

07:47.380 --> 07:51.009
WHAT'S WRONG, ALEX?
IS REALITY FINALLY SETTING IN?

07:51.010 --> 07:53.342
IT DOESN'T MATTER
IF I FIND THE REAL TERRORIST.

07:53.350 --> 07:55.250
THE WORLD THINKS
IT'S ME ANYWAY.

07:55.260 --> 07:57.080
YOU COULD HIRE
A P.R. GURU.

07:57.090 --> 07:59.763
I'M SURE RACHEL MADDOW
WOULD LOVE TO HAVE YOU ON.

07:59.770 --> 08:00.896
OR YOU COULD JUST WAIT

08:00.900 --> 08:02.356
AND TELL THE PRISONER
IN THE NEXT CELL

08:02.360 --> 08:03.304
AFTER YOU'RE CAUGHT.

08:03.310 --> 08:04.766
THERE WON'T BE A CELL,
SHELBY.

08:06.730 --> 08:08.470
THAT WAS RYAN.

08:10.660 --> 08:12.480
THE FBI WANTS ME DEAD.

08:12.490 --> 08:15.607
THE MOMENT THEY FIND ME,
I'M DONE.

08:19.240 --> 08:20.571
I NEED TO TALK TO SOMEONE.

08:20.580 --> 08:22.116
WHO?

08:22.120 --> 08:24.327
ANYONE WHO'LL LISTEN,

08:24.330 --> 08:27.163
ANYONE WHO CAN
CHANGE THE CONVERSATION.

08:27.170 --> 08:29.070
IF THE PUBLIC HEARS MY SIDE,

08:29.080 --> 08:31.628
IF THEY KNOW ME AS MORE
THAN JIHADI JANE,

08:31.630 --> 08:34.121
THEN -- THEN THE BUREAU
CAN'T JUST KILL ME.

08:38.680 --> 08:40.398
IT'S TIME TO TELL MY STORY.

08:59.710 --> 09:01.359
TOR?

09:01.370 --> 09:02.530
THE DARK WEB?

09:02.540 --> 09:04.861
YOU REALLY THINK
SOME ANONYMOUS HACKERS

09:04.870 --> 09:06.656
ARE GONNA
GET YOU OUT OF THIS?

09:06.660 --> 09:07.536
ACTUALLY, YES.

09:07.540 --> 09:09.280
BECAUSE THEY'RE
THE ONLY ONES

09:09.290 --> 09:11.463
WHO CAN ANONYMOUSLY
BROADCAST MY MESSAGE.

09:11.470 --> 09:13.791
THEY'RE ACTUALLY PEOPLE
WHO CARE ABOUT THE TRUTH.

09:13.800 --> 09:16.086
THEY DON'T JUST BLINDLY ACCEPT
THE OFFICIAL NARRATIVE.

09:17.800 --> 09:20.553
AND IF I FIND THEM,
I STAND A CHANCE.

09:20.560 --> 09:21.845
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

09:21.850 --> 09:23.886
OH, HERE WE GO.

09:28.810 --> 09:30.232
TAKE MY PICTURE.

09:31.490 --> 09:32.275
OOPS.

09:39.070 --> 09:39.957
[ GUN COCKS ]

09:39.960 --> 09:41.450
TAKE MY PICTURE.

09:43.620 --> 09:44.609
[ CELLPHONE CLICKS ]

09:44.620 --> 09:46.497
Liam:
GAINING SOMEONE'S TRUST --

09:46.500 --> 09:48.991
THAT'S WHAT BEING UNDERCOVER
IS ALL ABOUT,

09:49.000 --> 09:51.912
NOT PUTTING ON A COSTUME
OR SPEAKING WITH AN ACCENT.

09:51.920 --> 09:54.878
IT'S ABOUT
INHABITING A LIFE COMPLETELY.

09:54.880 --> 09:57.508
THAT'S WHY WHEN YOU GO
UNDERCOVER, YOU NEED TO HAVE

09:57.510 --> 10:01.719
A 360-DEGREE VIEW
OF WHO YOUR PERSONA IS.

10:01.720 --> 10:03.631
START WITH THE THINGS YOU KNOW

10:03.640 --> 10:06.598
AND USE THEM TO BUILD SOMEONE
WE DON'T KNOW.

10:06.600 --> 10:08.340
THINK OF THIS EXERCISE

10:08.350 --> 10:11.604
AS AN OPPORTUNITY TO EXPLORE
THE PATH NOT TAKEN.

10:11.610 --> 10:13.987
IT'S BAD ENOUGH
THAT I HAVE TO PLAY YOU --

10:13.990 --> 10:15.810
NOW I HAVE TO
PLAY SOMEONE ELSE, TOO.

10:15.820 --> 10:17.219
THAT MEANS STARTING WITH

10:17.230 --> 10:19.186
YOUR PERSONA'S
ACADEMIC BACKGROUND

10:19.190 --> 10:20.908
AND PROFESSIONAL AMBITIONS.

10:20.910 --> 10:22.537
YOU WANTED TO BE A LAWYER?
MM-HMM.

10:22.540 --> 10:24.076
REALLY?
YEAH !

10:24.080 --> 10:25.900
I LOVE TO ARGUE,
AND I'M REALLY GOOD AT IT.

10:25.910 --> 10:28.151
BUT THAT'S NOT ENOUGH.

10:28.160 --> 10:30.503
YOU HAVE TO KNOW YOUR PERSONA'S
LIKES AND DISLIKES.
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

10:30.510 --> 10:32.580
HEY, MAX!
ARE YOU SURE?

10:32.590 --> 10:34.956
THERE SHOULD BE A COPY ON HOLD
FOR SHELBY WYATT.

10:34.960 --> 10:36.200
YOU LOOKING FOR THIS?

10:36.210 --> 10:38.952
Liam: THEIR FAVORITE BOOK --
READ IT.

10:38.960 --> 10:41.963
WHO YOU ARE IS ALSO ABOUT
WHERE YOU'RE FROM.

10:41.970 --> 10:45.303
YOU HAVE TO KNOW YOUR HOMETOWN
INSIDE AND OUT.

10:45.310 --> 10:47.517
BUT IT GOES BEYOND
JUST THE FACTS.

10:47.520 --> 10:49.681
YOU HAVE TO SELL THIS PERSONA.

10:49.690 --> 10:54.639
9 TIMES OUT OF 10, WHAT BLOWS
A COVER IS HESITATION.

10:54.650 --> 10:57.938
NOW LET'S MEET
YOUR UNDERCOVER IDENTITIES.

10:57.940 --> 10:59.476
MY NAME IS JORDAN WEAVER.

10:59.480 --> 11:01.402
I SPENT FIVE YEARS
AS A HUMAN-RIGHTS ATTORNEY,

11:01.410 --> 11:02.570
AND NOW I WORK IN LEGAL.

11:02.580 --> 11:04.195
J.D. ROLLINS
FROM CONCORD, MASS.

11:04.200 --> 11:05.736
I STARTED OUT AS A CONTRACTOR

11:05.740 --> 11:07.867
AND SPENT THE LAST EIGHT YEARS
IN BUILDING OPS.

11:07.870 --> 11:08.939
MISS CASEY REGAN.

11:08.950 --> 11:10.167
I WORK AS A FINANCIAL ANALYST,

11:10.170 --> 11:11.660
BUT MY BACKGROUND
IS IN I-BANKING.

11:11.670 --> 11:13.160
[ Southern accent]
SAMUEL BERRY,

11:13.170 --> 11:14.910
BUT EVERYBODY JUST
CALLS ME SAM.

11:14.920 --> 11:17.206
I WORK IN DALLAS
WITH, UH, CORPORATE GIVING.

11:17.210 --> 11:18.700
DR. AVIVA CO RTAS.

11:18.710 --> 11:21.053
I WORK IN HUMAN RESOURCES
IN EGYPT.

11:21.060 --> 11:22.925
I USED TO TEACH RELIGION.

11:22.930 --> 11:24.386
WHAT'S ON YOUR
DVR RIGHT NOW?

11:24.390 --> 11:27.928
OH, I'M WATCHING THIS
INCREDIBLY POWERFUL DOCUMENTARY

11:27.930 --> 11:30.353
ON MASS EXECUTIONS IN INDONESIA.

11:30.360 --> 11:31.804
OH, AND -- AND "THE GOOD WIFE."

11:31.810 --> 11:33.141
WHAT STREET
DO YOU LIVE ON?

11:33.150 --> 11:35.687
SUNNWALE. UH, IT'S JUST OFF
OF ROBIN RIDGE ROAD.

11:35.690 --> 11:37.100
THAT'S NEAR EAST TRIPP DRIVE.

11:37.110 --> 11:37.929
IT'S JUST PAST
THE MIDDLE SCHOOL.

11:37.940 --> 11:38.679
YOU CAN'T MISS IT.

11:38.690 --> 11:40.362
DON'T SHOWBOAT.

11:40.370 --> 11:42.861
SAYING TOO MUCH IS JUST AS BAD
AS NOT SAYING ENOUGH.

11:42.870 --> 11:44.576
DO YOU BELIEVE IN GOD?

11:44.580 --> 11:46.696
I BELIEVE IN TOM BRADY
AND THE PATRIOTS.

11:46.700 --> 11:49.407
AND THE LAST YEAR HAS PROVEN
TO ME THAT GOD IS FALLIBLE.

11:49.410 --> 11:51.958
THAT REHEARSED LINE
CONSTITUTES A FUMBLE.

11:51.960 --> 11:53.746
WHO'D YOU GO
TO PROM WITH?

11:53.750 --> 11:55.035
DAVID O'NEIL.

11:55.040 --> 11:58.328
HE CHEATED ON ME IN THE BATHROOM
WITH LIBBY HOWARD.

11:58.330 --> 12:00.503
BUT I STILL BEAT HER OUT
FOR QUEEN.

12:00.510 --> 12:03.047
I MISSED MY PROM. I WAS
A STUDENT VOLUNTEER FOR OXFAM.

12:03.050 --> 12:05.041
TRICIA HAMILTON...AS FRIENDS.

12:05.050 --> 12:06.096
WE'D APPEAL THE CASE
TO THE NEXT HIGHER COURT.

12:06.100 --> 12:06.998
THE NIKKEI INDEX --

12:07.010 --> 12:08.295
SEXUAL HARASSMENT --

12:08.300 --> 12:10.052
IT'S BEEN REAL NICE
MEETING Y'ALL.

12:12.310 --> 12:14.551
CONGRATULATIONS.
YOU'VE ALL DONE WELL.

12:14.560 --> 12:16.721
BUT NOW IT'S TIME TO SEE
IF YOUR UNDERCOVER IDENTITIES

12:16.730 --> 12:19.107
CAN SURVIVE OUT HERE
IN THE REAL WORLD.

12:19.110 --> 12:20.611
IN THE HOTEL BEHIND ME

12:20.620 --> 12:23.271
IS THE ANNUAL
DYSTEK CORPORATE RETREAT.

12:23.280 --> 12:25.271
THE GOAL OF THIS EXERCISE
IS SIMPLE.

12:25.280 --> 12:28.113
GAIN A PRIVATE AUDIENCE
WITH THE C.E.O., NORMAN REED.

12:28.120 --> 12:29.519
IN ORDER FOR YOU TO DO SO,

12:29.530 --> 12:31.418
YOU'LL NEED TO
INFILTRATE THE EVENT,

12:31.420 --> 12:33.490
ESTABLISH YOURSELF
AS A DYSTEK EMPLOYEE,

12:33.500 --> 12:35.570
AND NETWORK YOUR WAY
TO A MEETING WITH MR. REED.

12:37.000 --> 12:38.661
IF YOU'RE GOING TO SUCCEED,

12:38.670 --> 12:40.331
YOU DON'T JUST NEED
THESE EMPLOYEES TO BELIEVE YOU.

12:40.340 --> 12:42.080
YOU'LL NEED THEM
TO LIKE YOU, TOO.

12:44.010 --> 12:46.331
OH, AND ONE MORE THING.

12:46.340 --> 12:49.082
IN THE FIELD, YOU OFTEN HAVE TO
GO UNDERCOVER QUICKLY

12:49.090 --> 12:51.058
WITHOUT TIME TO CRAFT A PERSONA.

12:51.060 --> 12:52.766
IT'S THE SAME WAY HERE.

12:52.770 --> 12:55.933
SO THOSE IDENTITIES
YOU CREATED TODAY...

12:55.940 --> 12:57.055
PASS THEM TO YOUR LEFT.

12:57.060 --> 12:58.596
WAIT, WHAT?

12:58.600 --> 12:59.589
GO AHEAD, PASS THEM.

12:59.600 --> 13:02.160
[ SIGHS ]

13:02.160 --> 13:05.778
NOW OPEN UP YOUR NOTEBOOKS
AND SAY HELLO TO THE NEW YOU.

13:05.780 --> 13:07.441
Raina: SARAH MEYERS?

13:10.170 --> 13:11.205
Duncan: HELLO?

13:14.410 --> 13:16.241
HELLO!

13:16.250 --> 13:17.399
OVER HERE.

13:21.880 --> 13:23.006
WHO'S THE BLONDE?

13:23.010 --> 13:25.126
I WOULD RATHER NOT
IDENTIFY MYSELF

13:25.130 --> 13:26.677
BEYOND
HER INSURANCE POLICY.

13:26.680 --> 13:28.500
DRAGGED HERFlIIAT GUNPOINT.

13:28.510 --> 13:30.057
WE'RE GONNA NEED
YOUR GUN.

13:30.060 --> 13:31.095
IF YOU'D LIKE,
I COULD HOLD ONTO IT.

13:31.100 --> 13:32.761
I CALL THE SHOTS HERE.

13:32.770 --> 13:34.135
Duncan: THERE'S A LOT OF THINGS
WE CAN DO FOR YOU, ALEX,

13:34.140 --> 13:35.095
BUT NONE OF THEM AT GUNPOINT.

13:36.890 --> 13:38.801
[ MAGAZINE CLICKS ]

13:47.860 --> 13:49.600
IS THAT WHAT YOU'RE GONNA USE
FOR THE BROADCAST?

13:49.610 --> 13:51.498
YEAH. ONCE YOU'VE ANSWERED
A FEW QUESTIONS.

13:51.500 --> 13:53.115
THAT WASN'T PART
OF THE ARRANGEMENT.

13:57.540 --> 14:00.373
WE HAVE A PLATFORM
THAT REACHES MILLIONS.

14:00.380 --> 14:02.041
ALL RIGHT?
IT'S A PLATFORM PEOPLE TRUST

14:02.050 --> 14:03.711
IN AN AGE WHERE
TRUST IS A RARE COMMODITY.

14:03.720 --> 14:05.290
WE CAN'T JUST
HAND THAT OVER TO YOU

14:05.300 --> 14:07.291
UNTIL WE'RE SURE
YOU DESERVE IT.

14:07.300 --> 14:08.870
SO YOU'RE GONNA PUT ME
ON TRIAL?

14:08.880 --> 14:10.677
IF YOU'RE INNOCENT,
WHAT DO YOU HAVE TO HIDE?

14:15.890 --> 14:17.096
LET'S GET STARTED.

14:21.440 --> 14:23.146
Duncan: HOW'D THE BLUEPRINTS
OF EXPLOSIVES

14:23.150 --> 14:24.390
WIND UP
IN YOUR APARTMENT?

14:24.400 --> 14:26.231
WHY DON'T YOU ASK
THE PERSON WHO FRAMED ME?

14:26.240 --> 14:27.468
SHOULD WE ALSO
ASK THAT PERSON

14:27.480 --> 14:29.983
HOW YOU WOUND UP UNCONSCIOUS
AT GRAND CENTRAL

14:29.990 --> 14:31.366
MOMENTS AFTER THE ATTACK?

14:31.370 --> 14:32.985
THAT INFORMATION
IS CLASSIFIED.

14:32.990 --> 14:35.402
[ SCOFFS ]
NOTHING'S CLASSIFIED.

14:35.410 --> 14:37.696
LOOK, YOU WANT ME TO PROVE
MY INNOCENCE? I CAN'T.

14:37.700 --> 14:40.919
IF YOU WANT TO TALK TO THEM,
YOU HAVE TO CONVINCE US FIRST.

14:40.920 --> 14:42.751
TELL US ABOUT
YOUR MISSING YEAR IN INDIA.

14:42.760 --> 14:45.547
WELL, NOT EXACTLY MISSING.
BACKPACKING THROUGH PAKISTAN?

14:45.550 --> 14:46.619
IRAN?

14:46.630 --> 14:48.291
WHAT ABOUT THE PEOPLE
YOU WERE WITH?

14:48.300 --> 14:49.585
SPECIFICALLY,
AMIR SALAAM.

14:49.590 --> 14:51.558
DID YOU KNOW HE HAD TIES
TO PAKISTANI INTELLIGENCE?

14:51.560 --> 14:52.959
DID YOU KNOW
HE WAS RESPONSIBLE

14:52.970 --> 14:55.302
FOR A CLUB BOMBING
IN BANGLADESH?

14:56.390 --> 14:59.507
[ DANCE MUSIC PLAYS ]

15:01.650 --> 15:04.062
Alex: SO,
OUT OF ALL THESE PEOPLE,

15:04.070 --> 15:05.469
WHO DO YOU THINK CAN
INTRODUCE US

15:05.480 --> 15:07.607
TO THE C.E.O.,
NORMAN REED?

15:07.610 --> 15:10.488
ALL RIGHT. WHAT ABOUT HER?
YELLOW JACKET.

15:10.490 --> 15:14.529
MIDDLE MANAGEMENT.
DON'T WASTE YOUR TIME ON THAT.

15:14.530 --> 15:17.693
OKAY. SEE HER TRYING TO FIND
SOMEONE TO TALK TO?

15:17.700 --> 15:21.204
AN EXECUTIVE DOESN'T HAVE TO.
PEOPLE COME TO THEM.

15:21.210 --> 15:23.792
WOW.
YOU DON'T MISS A BEAT.

15:25.210 --> 15:26.529
NO, I DON'T.

15:26.540 --> 15:27.586
YOU TRY.

15:27.590 --> 15:28.955
WHAT ABOUT HIM?

15:28.960 --> 15:29.961
THAT GUY RIGHT THERE?

15:29.970 --> 15:32.757
WELL-DRESSED, GOOD TAILOR,
MONEY.

15:32.760 --> 15:35.752
OKAY.
WELL-RESTED,
SO HE SETS HIS OWN HOURS.

15:35.760 --> 15:38.046
HE SEEMS IMPORTANT.

15:38.050 --> 15:41.816
I AGREE. WHICH IS WHY I'M GONNA
GO INTRODUCE MYSELF.

15:41.820 --> 15:43.720
REALLY? GREAT.
OKAY.

15:43.730 --> 15:46.221
I'M DR. AVIVA CORTAS.
NICE TO MEET YOU.

15:46.230 --> 15:48.312
MY BOYFRIEND'S
MEETING ME HERE TONIGHT.

15:48.320 --> 15:50.732
MAX?
THE ONE FROM NEW YORK?
YEAH.

15:50.740 --> 15:53.117
IF YOU HAVE TIME, I KNOW
HE'D LOVE TO MEET EVERYBODY.

15:53.120 --> 15:57.659
OKAY. BUT I'M WORKING NOW,
AND SO SHOULD YOU.

15:57.660 --> 16:00.458
YOU USED TO WORK IN ACADEMIA,
HUH?
YES, I DID.

16:00.460 --> 16:02.781
SO, HOW'S THE BACKSTABBING THERE
COMPARED TO HERE AT DYSTEK?

16:02.790 --> 16:04.371
OH. [ CHUCKLES ]

16:04.380 --> 16:05.916
UM, EVERYONE'S BEEN REALLY NICE
TO ME, ACTUALLY.

16:05.920 --> 16:07.626
PLEASE, DOCTOR.

16:07.630 --> 16:10.007
I'VE NEVER SEEN A COMPANY
THIS DYSFUNCTIONAL.

16:10.010 --> 16:12.422
IT MUST BE PARTICULARLY HARD
FOR YOU IN H.R.,

16:12.430 --> 16:14.000
WHAT,
WITH ALL THE TURNOVER.

16:14.010 --> 16:16.581
[ CHUCKLES ] I SUPPOSE.

16:16.590 --> 16:20.515
WHICH IS WHY I HAVE A PITCH
FOR A NEW HIRING INITIATIVE.

16:20.520 --> 16:22.932
YOU'RE FRIENDS WITH THE C.E.O.,
AREN'T YOU?

16:22.940 --> 16:24.555
[ LAUGHS ]

16:24.560 --> 16:25.970
WHERE'D THEY FIND YOU?

16:25.980 --> 16:28.392
SYRIA.
I WAS A HUMAN-RIGHTS LAWYER.

16:28.400 --> 16:29.469
HUMAN RIGHTS?
YEAH.

16:29.480 --> 16:31.107
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE
AT DYSTEK, THEN?

16:31.110 --> 16:32.407
UM, FOCUSING ON
THE WORKING CONDITIONS

16:32.410 --> 16:33.729
IN OUR CHINESE FACTORY.

16:33.740 --> 16:34.980
OH.

16:34.990 --> 16:37.527
AREN'T OUR FACTORIES
IN TAIWAN?

16:37.530 --> 16:42.240
SOME THINGS
AREN'T MEANT TO LAST FOREVER

16:42.250 --> 16:43.786
[ Southern accent]
GIN AND TONIC.

16:43.790 --> 16:45.451
LIGHT ON THE TONIC.

16:45.460 --> 16:47.951
NAME'S SAMANTHA.
WHERE ARE Y'ALL FROM?

16:47.960 --> 16:49.666
HOW LONG HAVE
YOU BEEN ON THE BOARD?!

16:49.670 --> 16:50.671
Woman: THE WHAT?!

16:50.680 --> 16:51.669
THE BOARD -- HOW LONG --

16:51.680 --> 16:53.796
NO, THANK YOU.
I ALREADY ATE.

16:53.800 --> 16:57.429
SOME HEARTS, THEY BURN
LIKE A WILDFIRE, WILDFIRE

16:57.430 --> 16:59.125
CALEB?
ELIAS?

17:00.230 --> 17:02.221
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

17:02.230 --> 17:04.471
LIAM THOUGHT THE ANALYSTS
SHOULD GET TO OBSERVE.

17:04.480 --> 17:08.393
SO TONIGHT, I'M GONNA
OBSERVE YOU...GOING DOWN.

17:10.150 --> 17:12.198
SPEAKING OF, LOOKS LIKE
KATE BLEW HER COVER.

17:12.200 --> 17:13.770
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]
OOH.

17:13.780 --> 17:15.145
WAIT. WAIT.

17:15.150 --> 17:17.948
ANOTHER 20 MINUTES,
THAT'S GONNA BE YOU, "SAMANTHA."

17:20.160 --> 17:21.320
[ CELLPHONE CHIMES ]

17:21.330 --> 17:22.615
Simon:
OH, MY BOYFRIEND'S HERE.

17:28.160 --> 17:30.583
MAX, YOU MADE IT.

17:32.930 --> 17:34.079
GLAD YOU COULD MAKE IT.

17:34.090 --> 17:35.717
I'VE NEVER TRAVELED THIS FAR
FOR A DATE.

17:35.720 --> 17:38.041
HM.
AND YOU BETTER BE WORTH IT.

17:38.050 --> 17:40.848
THE MOMENT THAT LEFT MY MOUTH,
I REGRETTED IT.

17:40.850 --> 17:42.977
IT'S COOL.

17:42.980 --> 17:44.095
I LIKE A CHALLENGE.

17:44.100 --> 17:45.556
YEAH.

17:45.560 --> 17:47.516
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

17:47.520 --> 17:49.841
I'LL GET YOUR BAG.
ARE YOU SURE?

17:54.280 --> 17:56.646
BURNIN' LIKE A WILDFIRE

17:56.650 --> 17:58.811
YOU KNOW EVERY GUY IN HERE
IS WATCHING YOU RIGHT NOW?

17:58.820 --> 18:00.321
WHERE WERE THEY
WHEN I PITCHED

18:00.330 --> 18:02.491
THE REDESIGN
OF OUR CORPORATE BRANDING?

18:02.500 --> 18:04.786
MAYBE IF THE C.E.O.
HAD BEEN THERE,

18:04.790 --> 18:06.189
THEY WOULD HAVE
PAID MORE ATTENTION.

18:06.200 --> 18:07.531
HAVE YOU EVER MET NORMAN?

18:07.540 --> 18:09.610
YOU KNOW I'M LIKE
HIS RIGHT HAND, RIGHT?

18:09.620 --> 18:11.918
HE'S AT A DINNER WITH
THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS NOW,

18:11.920 --> 18:13.205
BUT HE'LL BE BACK LATER.

18:13.210 --> 18:15.166
DO YOU WANT TO MEET HIM?

18:15.170 --> 18:16.501
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATES ]
YES.

18:17.670 --> 18:19.626
EXCUSE ME.

18:22.680 --> 18:24.261
WHAT THE...?

18:24.270 --> 18:26.477
I TOLD YOU,
IT LOOKS BETTER ON ME.

18:26.480 --> 18:29.347
THIS IS MY NIGHT, NIMAH.
WE AGREED.

18:29.350 --> 18:31.648
LADIES!

18:31.650 --> 18:33.777
YOU WERE NOT RECRUITED
TO BE TRADITIONAL AGENTS,

18:33.780 --> 18:35.600
AND YOU WILL NOT BE TRAINED
THAT WAY.

18:35.610 --> 18:38.272
THE WHOLE POINT
OF HAVING TWINS

18:38.280 --> 18:41.408
IS SO THAT ONE OF YOU
WILL ALWAYS BE UNDERCOVER,
COLLECTING INTEL,

18:41.410 --> 18:43.787
WHILE THE OTHER ONE
REPORTS BACK TO THE FBI.

18:43.790 --> 18:47.578
SO TONIGHT, YOU WILL TRADE
PLACES EVERY HOUR ON THE HOUR.

18:47.580 --> 18:49.536
LIKE IN A REAL OPERATION,

18:49.540 --> 18:51.087
YOU CAN ONLY BRIEF EACH OTHER
IN PASSING.

18:51.090 --> 18:53.957
THE CHALLENGE WILL BE
TO QUICKLY COMMUNICATE

18:53.960 --> 18:56.838
ALL NECESSARY INFORMATION
TO MAINTAIN COVER.

18:56.840 --> 18:59.707
UNLIKE THE OTHER NATS...

18:59.710 --> 19:04.090
IF YOU'RE CAUGHT TONIGHT,
YOU'RE OUT OF THE ACADEMY.

19:04.100 --> 19:06.136
WE CAN'T SEND AGENTS
INTO TERRORIST CELLS

19:06.140 --> 19:09.382
IF THEY CAN'T SURVIVE
A COCKTAIL PARTY.

19:09.390 --> 19:13.178
AND...YOU BOTH LOOK BEAUTIFUL.

19:15.570 --> 19:17.390
[ FOOTSTEPS RECEDING ]

19:17.400 --> 19:20.984
YOU SAID YOU'D STEP IT UP.
NOW IS THE TIME.

19:20.990 --> 19:23.572
TELL ME
WHAT I NEED TO KNOW.

19:23.580 --> 19:25.980
BUT WHAT IS THE POINT OF
A CHARITABLE-GIVING PROGRAM

19:25.990 --> 19:28.481
IF YOU DON'T TRACK THE IMPACT?
AM I RIGHT?

19:28.490 --> 19:31.288
SAMANTHA, WE SHOULD KICK SOME OF
THESE IDEAS UP TO NORMAN.

19:31.290 --> 19:32.951
DON'T LISTEN
TO A WORD SHE SAYS.

19:32.960 --> 19:34.951
SHE STOLE MY IDEA,
AND I CAN PROVE IT.

19:34.960 --> 19:39.078
I HAVE MY LAWYER
ON THE PHONE RIGHT NOW.

19:39.090 --> 19:41.558
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
ANALYSTS ARE HERE TO WATCH.

19:41.560 --> 19:43.630
I AM WATCHING.
I'M WATCHING YOU FAIL.

19:43.640 --> 19:45.005
TURNABOUT IS FAIR PLAY.

19:45.010 --> 19:47.058
I'M SURPRISED YOU EVEN KNOW
WHAT THAT MEANS.

19:47.060 --> 19:50.644
WHAT YOU GONNA DO
HANK, THERE'S SOMEONE HERE YOU
GOT TO MEET.

19:50.650 --> 19:52.686
JORDAN WEAVER, THIS
IS HANK HADLEY,
HEAD OF DEVELOPMENT.

19:52.690 --> 19:53.679
PLEASURE TO MEET YOU.

19:53.690 --> 19:54.896
AND I'D LIKE YOU
TO MEET, UH...

19:54.900 --> 19:56.720
DR. AVIVA CO RTAS.

19:56.730 --> 19:58.015
PLEASURE TO MEET YOU.

19:58.020 --> 20:00.739
JORDAN WEAVER.
YOU AS WELL.

20:00.740 --> 20:03.698
THE DOCTOR HERE
HAS GREAT IDEAS.

20:03.700 --> 20:05.440
LET'S GET HER UP
TO MEET NORMAN.
OKAY.

20:08.160 --> 20:10.663
TELL ME WHY

20:13.090 --> 20:15.206
WE CAN'T MAKE THIS WORK

20:17.590 --> 20:19.410
Liam: I THOUGHT YOU DIDN'T
LIKE IT WHEN I DRINK.

20:19.420 --> 20:22.389
I DON'T,
BUT I NEED YOU TO TALK.

20:22.390 --> 20:24.039
AND IN MY EXPERIENCE,
THIS IS THE BEST WAY.

20:28.260 --> 20:30.262
REMEMBER WHEN
WE USED TO COME HERE?

20:30.270 --> 20:32.898
FEELS LIKE OLD TIMES.

20:32.900 --> 20:35.141
THE LAST TIME
WE WERE HERE,

20:35.150 --> 20:38.972
REMEMBER,
WE DECIDED TO END OUR MARRIAGES.

20:38.980 --> 20:41.448
AND YOU ALMOST DID.

20:41.450 --> 20:43.315
AND YOU DIDN'T.
I JUST NEEDED MORE TIME.

20:43.320 --> 20:45.447
[ SIGHS ] SO YOU SAID.

20:47.780 --> 20:50.237
AND I GAVE YOU
THE BENEFIT OF THE DOUBT,

20:50.240 --> 20:52.071
A MISTAKE
THAT I WILL NEVER MAKE AGAIN.

20:52.080 --> 20:54.913
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

20:54.920 --> 20:57.821
WHY ARE YOU RUNNING AN OFF-BOOK
OPERATION ON ALEX PARRISH?

20:57.830 --> 21:00.242
DOES SHE POSE SOME THREAT
I'M NOT AWARE OF?

21:00.250 --> 21:01.638
DOES SHE HAVE SOMETHING
ON YOU?

21:03.220 --> 21:05.085
LIAM .

21:07.220 --> 21:08.369
[ SIGHS ]

21:08.380 --> 21:10.723
IT'S NOT JUST ME
SHE HAS SOMETHING ON.

21:14.850 --> 21:16.181
IT'S ALL OF US.

21:19.150 --> 21:21.732
BUY ME ANOTHER DRINK,
AND I'LL TELL YOU EVERYTHING.

21:24.110 --> 21:25.657
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

21:25.660 --> 21:26.695
Max: HELLO?

21:26.700 --> 21:29.066
MAX?

21:29.070 --> 21:30.708
MAX?

21:30.710 --> 21:33.281
UM, WHO ARE YOU,
AND HOW DO YOU KNOW MY NAME?

21:33.290 --> 21:35.110
SIMON AND I
WORK TOGETHER.

21:35.120 --> 21:36.951
WE'RE FRIENDS.
ELIAS.

21:36.960 --> 21:38.245
MAYBE YOU'VE HEARD OF ME?

21:38.250 --> 21:39.865
NO? OKAY.

21:39.870 --> 21:41.417
WELL, SIMON'S STUCK
DOWNSTAIRS,

21:41.420 --> 21:43.797
SO HE TOLD ME TO COME ENTERTAIN
YOU FOR A LITTLE WHILE.

21:43.800 --> 21:46.416
UH, HE TOLD ME TO STAY
IN THE ROOM UNTIL HE GOT BACK.

21:46.420 --> 21:49.753
I CAN ENTERTAIN YOU IN THE ROOM,
CAN'T I?

21:49.760 --> 21:51.842
[ CHUCKLES ]

21:53.690 --> 21:55.055
Liam: LISTEN UP!

21:55.060 --> 21:57.847
WE'VE JUST RECEIVED INTEL

21:57.850 --> 22:00.899
THAT PARRISH IS COLLUDING WITH
THE UNKNOWN HERE IN NEW YORK.

22:00.900 --> 22:03.061
WHEN DID YOU LAST SEE
AMIR?

22:03.070 --> 22:05.391
MARCH 3, 2008.

22:05.400 --> 22:07.231
SO, YOU HAD NO CONTACT WITH HIM
BETWEEN THEN AND LAST YEAR

22:07.240 --> 22:08.309
WHEN HE WAS KILLED
IN BAJAUR?

22:08.320 --> 22:10.231
HE WASN'T
WHAT YOU THINK HE WAS.

22:10.240 --> 22:14.449
AS WE SPEAK, THEY ARE PREPARING
TO STREAM A LIVE INTERVIEW.

22:14.450 --> 22:17.032
NOW, THE BAD NEWS IS THAT
THEY HAVE THE TOOLS

22:17.040 --> 22:18.405
TO COVER THEIR TRACKS.

22:18.410 --> 22:19.616
YOU MUST HAVE BEEN MAD.

22:19.620 --> 22:21.212
YOU MUST HAVE WANTED
TO GET EVEN.

22:21.220 --> 22:25.042
THE GOOD NEWS IS,
THEY CANNOT COVER THEM FOR LONG.

22:25.050 --> 22:27.666
I SPENT A DECADE IN INDIA.

22:27.670 --> 22:30.423
I TRAVELED TO PAKISTAN.
I TRAVELED TO IRAN.

22:30.430 --> 22:32.887
I WANTED TO FIND OUT
MORE ABOUT THE WORLD,

22:32.890 --> 22:34.426
FORM MY OWN OPINIONS.

22:34.430 --> 22:37.422
AND ALONG THE WAY,
I MET PEOPLE.

22:37.430 --> 22:39.341
YOU CAN LABEL THEM
AS YOU WANT,

22:39.350 --> 22:41.568
BUT MY EXPERIENCE
WAS MY OWN.

22:41.570 --> 22:44.528
10 OF THE PEOPLE I MET
HAVE SINCE BEEN KILLED.

22:44.530 --> 22:47.681
THREE, INCLUDING AMIR,
IN DRONE STRIKES.

22:49.900 --> 22:52.403
I'M SURE YOU'RE NOT SAYING
THAT JUST BECAUSE I KNEW THEM,

22:52.410 --> 22:54.071
I WAS A TERRORIST.

22:54.080 --> 22:56.036
HELL, I DON'T EVEN THINK
THEY WERE TERRORISTS.

22:56.040 --> 22:59.578
IT'S JUST EASY TO BLAME THEM,
LIKE IT'S EASY TO BLAME ME.

23:02.500 --> 23:05.799
NOW TURN ON THAT CAMERA,
OR I WALK.

23:05.800 --> 23:08.371
AS SOON AS THEY GO LIVE,
WE CAN ISOLATE

23:08.380 --> 23:11.269
THE ORIGIN OF THE BROADCAST
WITHIN FIVE MINUTES.

23:11.270 --> 23:15.218
THEY JUST HAVE TO STAY ON
FOR THAT LONG -- FIVE MINUTES.

23:15.220 --> 23:17.051
WE GOT HER.

23:20.900 --> 23:23.107
[ LIGHT SWITCH CLICKS ]

23:24.900 --> 23:27.471
AND WE GO LIVE
IN 60 SECONDS.

23:33.490 --> 23:37.403
IF YOU DIDN'T
BOMB GRAND CENTRAL, WHO DID?

23:37.410 --> 23:39.822
THE MORNING OF THE BOMBING,
THE FBI GOT A TIP

23:39.830 --> 23:43.743
THAT THE BOMBER WAS SOMEONE
FROM MY CLASS AT THE ACADEMY.

23:43.750 --> 23:46.492
EVERYTHING THAT I'VE FOUND
SO FAR SUPPORTS THAT THEORY.

23:46.500 --> 23:48.957
THE BOMBER KNEW EXACTLY WHAT
THEY WERE DOING FROM DAY ONE.

23:48.960 --> 23:50.882
WHY DO YOU SAY THAT?

23:50.890 --> 23:52.755
THEY FRAMED THE BROWN GIRL.

23:52.760 --> 23:57.345
I'D SPENT TIME
IN INDIA AND PAKISTAN.

23:57.350 --> 24:00.342
IN THIS COUNTRY,
I'M AN EASY PERSON TO BLAME.

24:00.350 --> 24:02.352
50, ONE OF YOUR OWN CLASSMATES
BETRAYED YOU?

24:02.360 --> 24:04.146
I GUESS.

24:04.150 --> 24:06.721
THE CLOSER I WAS TO SOMEONE
AT THE ACADEMY,

24:06.730 --> 24:09.938
THE EASIER IT WOULD HAVE BEEN
FOR THEM TO FRAME ME.

24:09.940 --> 24:12.158
THAT'S WHY IT'S SO HARD
TO TRUST ANYONE RIGHT NOW.

24:12.160 --> 24:15.482
IMAGINE
IF A FRIEND LIED TO YOU

24:15.490 --> 24:19.608
FROM THE FIRST MOMENT
THEY LAID EYES ON YOU.

24:19.620 --> 24:21.838
IMAGINE IF THEY WERE
STILL LYING TO YOU.

24:21.840 --> 24:24.991
AND WORSE,
THE PEOPLE WHO KNEW YOU BEST

24:25.000 --> 24:27.833
DIDN'T BELIEVE YOU,
NO MATTER WHAT YOU SAID.

24:30.890 --> 24:32.846
I'M IN A NIGHTMARE.

24:32.850 --> 24:36.843
WE'RE STREAMING TO OVER
12 MILLION PEOPLE RIGHT NOW.

24:36.850 --> 24:39.580
AND IF YOU COULD SAY ANYTHING
TO THEM, WHAT WOULD IT BE?

24:39.590 --> 24:42.013
I LOVE THIS COUNTRY.

24:42.020 --> 24:45.262
AND I WANT TO PROTECT IT.

24:45.270 --> 24:48.353
THAT'S WHY I BECAME AN FBI AGENT
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

24:49.940 --> 24:52.864
SHOULDN'T SHOOT FIRST
AND ASK QUESTIONS LATER.

24:52.870 --> 24:56.192
IF IT WERE UP TO THE FBI,
I'D BE DEAD ALREADY.

24:57.700 --> 24:59.440
THAT'S WHY I HOPE
THAT THIS INTERVIEW

24:59.450 --> 25:02.032
MAKES THEM THINK TWICE
ABOUT SILENCING ME

25:02.040 --> 25:05.203
BEFORE THE TRUTH COMES OUT.

25:05.210 --> 25:08.111
I AM INNOCENT.

25:08.120 --> 25:10.281
[ DANCE MUSIC PLAYS ]

25:10.290 --> 25:11.962
NOW THAT I'M
A LITTLE DRUNK,

25:11.970 --> 25:14.882
I CAN TELL YOU THIS --
FORGET NORMAN.

25:14.890 --> 25:16.289
OKAY, HE'S...

25:16.300 --> 25:19.121
HE'S ON HIS WAY OUT.
YOU DON'T NEED HIM.

25:19.130 --> 25:21.473
BUT HE'S STILL
THE C.E.O. TONIGHT, RIGHT?
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATES ]

25:21.480 --> 25:22.390
SURE.

25:24.100 --> 25:26.432
THE NEXT ONE IS ON ME.

25:26.440 --> 25:28.761
SHE HAS
A 4-YEAR-OLD DAUGHTER -- AVERY.

25:28.770 --> 25:31.603
THE FATHER'S MIKE --
TOTAL DEADBEAT.

25:31.610 --> 25:33.566
SHE HATES THE C.E.O.
AND THINKS HE'S GONNA BE FIRED.

25:33.570 --> 25:35.140
OKAY.

25:35.150 --> 25:37.232
[ INHALES,
EXHALES DEEPLY ]

25:37.240 --> 25:38.980
HERE YOU GO.

25:40.620 --> 25:42.656
THAT'S INSANE.
[ CHUCKLES ]

25:42.660 --> 25:45.823
SO, YOU AND SIMON DIDN'T
KNOW EACH OTHER AT ALL?

25:45.830 --> 25:48.537
HE MESSAGED ME ONCE OUT OF
THE BLUE -- MUTUAL FRIEND --

25:48.540 --> 25:50.758
AND ASKED ME TO TAKE A PHOTO
WITH HIM BY GRAND CENTRAL

25:50.760 --> 25:52.466
OF ALL PLACES.

25:52.470 --> 25:54.006
AND THEN HE TAKES OFF.

25:54.010 --> 25:56.126
AFTER NOT HEARING FROM HIM
FOR WEEKS,

25:56.130 --> 25:58.428
HE REACHES OUT
AND ASKS ME TO MEET HIM HERE.

25:58.430 --> 26:00.421
I'M SUDDENLY REALIZING
HOW PATHETIC THAT SOUNDS.

26:00.430 --> 26:02.842
WHO GETS ON A TRAIN
TO MEET A GUY THEY BARELY KNOW?

26:02.850 --> 26:05.762
SIMON'S FASCINATING.

26:05.770 --> 26:07.226
I GET IT.

26:07.230 --> 26:08.845
I SAW IT
THE SECOND I MET HIM.

26:08.850 --> 26:11.603
SO, I FIGURED, WHY NOT?

26:11.610 --> 26:13.942
AT LEAST I'D HAVE A STORY
TO TELL MY FRIENDS ON MONDAY.

26:13.950 --> 26:15.440
WHICH IT TURNS OUT I DO,

26:15.450 --> 26:17.486
SINCE HE INVITED ME
TO HIS CORPORATE RETREAT,

26:17.490 --> 26:19.526
SURROUNDED BY
ALL HIS CO-WORKERS,

26:19.530 --> 26:22.499
LIKE YOU, WHO HE WANTS
TO INTRODUCE ME TO LATER.

26:22.500 --> 26:24.991
WELL, AT LEAST
YOU'RE NOT UP HERE ALONE.

26:27.910 --> 26:30.401
SO, WITH THE MONEY FROM
THE CHARITABLE TAX REBATE,

26:30.410 --> 26:32.378
I'M THINKING WE HAVE
A FEW OPTIONS --

26:32.380 --> 26:34.541
SAMANTHA,
WHAT ON EARTH ARE YOU DOING?

26:34.550 --> 26:36.461
THE DOCTOR TOLD YOU YOU AIN'T
SUPPOSED TO BE DRINKING

26:36.470 --> 26:38.199
WHILE
YOU'RE BREAST-FEEDING.

26:38.210 --> 26:40.633
DO I NEED TO TAKE YOU BACK
TO REHAB RIGHT NOW?

26:40.640 --> 26:41.846
[ GASPS ]

26:44.180 --> 26:45.841
WHAT THE HELL
IS YOUR PROBLEM?!

26:45.850 --> 26:47.169
OH, H DON'T HAVE
A PROBLEM.

26:47.180 --> 26:48.306
THAT'S JUST PAYBACK.

26:48.310 --> 26:49.595
THIS ISN'T ABOUT
THIS MORNING.

26:49.600 --> 26:51.568
THIS ISN'T ABOUT ANYTHING
OTHER THAN THE FACT

26:51.570 --> 26:52.889
THAT YOU'RE NOT
A NAT ANYMORE.

26:52.900 --> 26:55.107
BUT GUESS WHAT, BUDDY --
THAT IS YOUR FAULT.

26:55.110 --> 26:56.771
THE ONLY REASON
I'M NOT A NAT ANYMORE

26:56.780 --> 26:58.270
IS 'CAUSE A MORMON
EXPLODED ON ME.

26:58.280 --> 27:00.066
YOU DROVE A MAN
TO SUICIDE!

27:00.070 --> 27:02.197
YEAH, WELL,
YOU'D DRIVE A MAN TO MURDER.

27:02.200 --> 27:03.906
OH,
YOU ARE SUCH AN IDIOT.

27:03.910 --> 27:05.446
I'M AN IDIOT SAVANT.

27:05.450 --> 27:07.862
YOU LOOK STUPID
IN THAT SHIRT.

27:07.870 --> 27:10.156
WELL, YOU LOOK STUPID,
PERIOD.

27:10.160 --> 27:11.502
[ LAUGHS ]

27:11.510 --> 27:12.954
OH, MY GOD.
I JUST CAN'T STAND YOU!

27:12.960 --> 27:15.167
SO SHUT ME UP ALREADY.

27:17.880 --> 27:21.964
AHH, AW, YEAH

27:21.970 --> 27:25.679
ALL RIGHT

27:25.680 --> 27:28.808
YEAH

27:28.810 --> 27:32.928
THE LEAVES,
THEY DON'T CHANGE YOU

27:32.940 --> 27:39.106
THE LEAVES DON'T CHANGE YOU,
SO I NEVER SAW IT COMING

27:40.910 --> 27:44.152
WINTER HIT ME, HIROSHIMA

27:44.160 --> 27:47.277
WHERE DID THE SUN GO?

27:47.280 --> 27:50.738
JUST A CRUEL RAIN POURING

27:50.750 --> 27:55.335
YOU SAY THAT IT'S OVER

27:55.340 --> 27:58.127
WE MADE IT.
WE GET TO MEET THE C.E.O.

27:58.130 --> 27:59.586
LOOKS LIKE IT.
[ CHUCKLES ]

27:59.590 --> 28:03.003
WHEN I NEVER SAW IT COMING
BAD NEWS.

28:03.010 --> 28:05.001
I'M AFRAID NORMAN
WON'T BE COMING BACK TONIGHT.

28:05.010 --> 28:06.841
WHAT? WHY IS THAT?

28:06.850 --> 28:09.091
YOU'LL FIND OUT
SOON ENOUGH, I GUESS.

28:09.100 --> 28:10.931
THE BOARD JUST LET HIM GO.

28:10.940 --> 28:15.149
BUT IF YOU'RE LOOKING
TO TALK TO THE NEW C.E.O.,

28:15.150 --> 28:16.765
WELL,
I GUESS YOU ALREADY HAVE.

28:16.770 --> 28:18.806
WAIT. IT'S YOU?

28:18.810 --> 28:21.779
[ GASPS ] I WON.

28:21.780 --> 28:23.111
W-WON WHAT?

28:23.120 --> 28:24.690
MY GOD.
I HAVE SO MUCH TO DO.

28:24.700 --> 28:26.691
I HAVE NO IDEA
WHERE TO START.

28:26.700 --> 28:28.941
YOU, COME DOWNSTAIRS.

28:28.950 --> 28:30.747
SHOW ME SOME OF THOSE
LOGO IDEAS.

28:30.750 --> 28:33.958
I NEED TO RE-BRAND
RIGHT AWAY.

28:33.960 --> 28:35.780
WELL, I GUESS WE ALL WON.

28:35.790 --> 28:38.873
LOOKS LIKE WE DID.

28:38.880 --> 28:41.257
SO, SHOULD WE GO BACK DOWNSTAIRS
AND RUB THEIR NOSES IN IT?

28:41.260 --> 28:44.297
WHAT'S THE RUSH, AVIVA?

28:44.300 --> 28:47.428
DROWNING IN MY SORROWS
WE HAVE THE WHOLE BAR
TO OURSELVES RIGHT HERE.

28:47.430 --> 28:50.979
EAGER WAVES
KEEP ON CRASHING

28:50.980 --> 28:52.936
[ SIREN WAILS ]
Man: WE FOUND THE SOURCE
OF THE UNKNOWN TRANSMISSION.

28:52.940 --> 28:54.555
[ TIRES SCREECH ]
PULLING UP THERE NOW.

28:54.560 --> 28:55.800
GO, GO, GO!

28:55.810 --> 28:57.107
NOW, NOW. LET'S GO!

28:57.110 --> 28:59.556
[ MAN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY ]

28:59.560 --> 29:02.859
THIS IS THE FBI.
WE HAVE YOU SURROUNDED.

29:02.860 --> 29:04.987
PUT YOUR HANDS UP
AND COME OUT NOW.

29:04.990 --> 29:06.560
I'M SORRY,
THEY SHOULDN'T HAVE BEEN ABLE

29:06.570 --> 29:07.810
TO TRACE THE SIGNAL
THAT QUICKLY.

29:07.820 --> 29:09.026
IT'S OKAY.

29:09.030 --> 29:10.349
I KNEW THIS MIGHT HAPPEN.

29:10.360 --> 29:11.622
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

29:11.630 --> 29:13.074
I DON'T HAVE TO DO ANYTHING.

29:14.920 --> 29:17.241
[ RADIO CHATTER ]

29:21.550 --> 29:23.711
SHE'S SMART.

29:23.720 --> 29:24.709
I'LL GIVE HER THAT.

29:24.720 --> 29:26.335
WELL,
THIS IS A P.R. NIGHTMARE.

29:26.340 --> 29:27.079
MORE THAN YOU KNOW.

29:28.470 --> 29:29.755
RAMADAN .

29:39.390 --> 29:41.608
IT'S A MATTER
OF NATIONAL SECURITY.

29:41.610 --> 29:44.568
THEN YOU SHOULD HAVE NO TROUBLE
OBTAINING A WARRANT.

29:44.570 --> 29:47.391
IMAM DARR, YOU'VE ALWAYS BEEN
A FRIEND OF THE BUREAU.

29:47.400 --> 29:49.607
AND THE RASH OF VIOLENCE
AND RACIAL PROFILING

29:49.610 --> 29:52.329
AGAINST OUR COMMUNITY
IN THE PAST 24 HOURS

29:52.330 --> 29:54.616
HAS MADE ME
RETHINK MY POSITION.

29:54.620 --> 29:56.668
GET ME JUDGE RAKOFF.

29:56.670 --> 29:58.319
WE'RE TAKING THOSE DOORS
IN 60 SECONDS EITHER WAY --

29:58.330 --> 30:00.116
I DON'T CARE.
O'CONNOR, LOOK.

30:01.800 --> 30:03.586
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

30:05.300 --> 30:07.507
[ REPORTERS SHOUTING
INDISTINCTLY ]

30:07.510 --> 30:09.831
EVERYBODY BACK! BACK!

30:09.840 --> 30:12.388
GET BACK, GET BACK.

30:12.390 --> 30:14.096
STAND DOWN! GO!
[ VEHICLE DOORS CLOSING ]

30:16.480 --> 30:19.597
LET'S GO. YOU HEARD HIM.
LET'S GO. LET'S GO. LET'S GO.

30:19.600 --> 30:20.476
BACK.

30:23.780 --> 30:27.068
ASHER, BOOTH, GIVE ME EYES!

30:28.030 --> 30:29.486
[ HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING ]

30:29.490 --> 30:30.809
ANYBODY SEEING HER?

30:30.820 --> 30:32.151
ARE YOU ROLLING?
ARE YOU ROLLING?

30:32.160 --> 30:33.900
ARE YOU GETTING THIS?

30:33.910 --> 30:37.744
OKAY, THERE APPEARS TO BE
A STANDOFF BETWEEN THE FBI...

30:40.540 --> 30:42.838
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

30:44.760 --> 30:46.000
GOT TO LET THEM PASS.

30:46.010 --> 30:47.216
HEY.

30:48.300 --> 30:50.256
IT'S OKAY. IT'S OKAY.
GO ON. GO ON.

30:50.260 --> 30:52.091
Man:
ANYBODY GOT EYES ON HER?

30:52.100 --> 30:53.226
GO AHEAD. IT'S ALL RIGHT.
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

30:53.230 --> 30:53.969
DON'T BE AFRAID.
DON'T BE AFRAID.

30:53.970 --> 30:55.631
EVERYBODY STAY CALM.

30:55.640 --> 30:56.459
ASHER!

30:58.810 --> 30:59.595
THAT'S A NEGATIVE.

31:00.850 --> 31:02.738
WHERE IS SHE?!

31:02.740 --> 31:04.139
WE LOST HER.

31:06.280 --> 31:07.474
AGENT: Parrish is gone,

31:07.480 --> 31:09.528
but we found Agent Wyatt
in the basement.

31:09.530 --> 31:11.361
EXCUSE ME.
I'M SORRY.

31:11.370 --> 31:12.530
SORRY.

31:14.080 --> 31:16.287
WE PROVED SOMETHING
TONIGHT.

31:16.290 --> 31:19.487
WE SWITCHED PLACES FIVE TIMES
WITHOUT ANYONE NOTICING.

31:19.490 --> 31:21.663
WE CAN DO THIS.

31:21.670 --> 31:24.377
NOW WE JUST NEED
TO GET OUT OF THESE CLOTHES.

31:24.380 --> 31:27.292
I THINK SIMON WOULD LIKE
TO HELP WITH THAT.

31:27.300 --> 31:30.292
SIMON DOESN'T LIKE PEOPLE
LIKE ME.

31:30.300 --> 31:32.552
SIMON LIKES YOU.

31:32.560 --> 31:34.960
AND IF YOU WANT TO
SPEND MORE TIME WITH HIM,

31:34.970 --> 31:37.177
I'LL MAKE IT WORK.

31:38.810 --> 31:40.346
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

31:42.480 --> 31:44.607
Elias:
LOOKING FOR MAX?

31:44.610 --> 31:46.771
HE CAME AND WENT.

31:46.780 --> 31:49.726
HERE'S THE THING
THAT BOTHERS ME.

31:49.730 --> 31:52.119
IT'S NOT JUST YOU LYING
ABOUT BEING GAY.

31:52.120 --> 31:53.485
DON'T GET ME WRONG,

31:53.490 --> 31:56.982
THAT DEEPLY OFFENDS ME
AS A GAY MAN,

31:56.990 --> 31:59.572
A MAN WHO WAS ACTUALLY
BULLIED,

31:59.580 --> 32:03.084
A MAN WHO ACTUALLY FOUGHT
FOR MARRIAGE EQUALITY,

32:03.090 --> 32:06.878
A MAN WHO'S ACTUALLY DONE THINGS
TO ANOTHER MAN,

32:06.880 --> 32:08.871
AND RECENTLY, TOO.

32:08.880 --> 32:10.745
LOOK, ELIAS, THIS IS --

32:10.750 --> 32:14.254
AND IT'S NOT HOW YOU'RE ABOUT
TO SUGGEST LIFE IS COMPLICATED.

32:14.260 --> 32:15.841
OR THAT YOU'RE BISEXUAL.

32:15.850 --> 32:17.135
I'M NOT GONNA SAY IT.

32:17.140 --> 32:18.300
NO. UNH-UNH.

32:18.310 --> 32:21.473
DON'T CO-OPT
THAT STRUGGLE, TOO.

32:21.480 --> 32:23.857
NO.

32:23.860 --> 32:27.899
THE THING THAT BUGS ME IS
THE LENGTHS YOU'RE WILLING TO GO

32:27.900 --> 32:30.437
TO MAINTAIN THIS FACADE.

32:30.440 --> 32:34.274
YOU MANIPULATED A COMPLETE
STRANGER TO COME HERE,

32:34.280 --> 32:37.067
AN INNOCENT PERSON.

32:37.070 --> 32:38.651
WHO DOES THAT?

32:38.660 --> 32:41.288
YOU WANT TO KNOW THE TRUTH,
SIMON?

32:41.290 --> 32:43.781
THE TRUTH IS...

32:43.790 --> 32:45.496
YOU'RE DANGEROUS.

32:45.500 --> 32:47.411
SO WHEN WE GET BACK
TOMORROW,

32:47.420 --> 32:50.571
I'M MAKING SURE YOU NEVER
STEP FOOT IN QUANTICO AGAIN.

32:57.220 --> 32:58.926
[ DOOR OPENS ]

33:01.730 --> 33:04.221
QUITE A VIEW, HUH?

33:06.560 --> 33:08.300
ONE OF THE PERKS
OF WORKING FOR

33:08.310 --> 33:10.392
THE GENERAL COUNSELOR'S OFFICE,
DR. CORTAS.

33:10.400 --> 33:13.904
SHE SAID,
I DON'T WANT A MODEL

33:13.910 --> 33:17.152
I DON'T WANT A MOVIE STAR

33:17.160 --> 33:19.526
YOU DON'T HAVE TO
WIN THE LOTTO
THIS YOUR FIRST TIME
AT ONE OF THESE RETREATS?

33:19.530 --> 33:22.203
OH, I WANT YOU TO
WIN MY HEART, YEAH
[ GASPS ]
IS IT THAT OBVIOUS?

33:22.210 --> 33:23.416
OH, MY GOD.

33:23.420 --> 33:26.912
WELL, I KNOW
THEY AREN'T MUCH FUN, BUT...

33:26.920 --> 33:30.162
IT'S NICE TO ESCAPE
FOR THE WEEKEND.

33:30.170 --> 33:32.331
SHE SAID I JUST WANT
SOMEONE TO SMOKE WITH ME, BABE

33:32.340 --> 33:35.548
WHAT ARE YOU ESCAPING FROM,
JORDAN?

33:35.550 --> 33:36.619
KIDS?

33:36.630 --> 33:38.678
AND LAY WITH ME, BABE
A WIFE?

33:38.680 --> 33:41.308
LAUGH WITH ME, BABE

33:41.310 --> 33:42.516
EX-WIFE.

33:42.520 --> 33:44.476
I JUST WANT
THE SIMPLE THINGS

33:44.480 --> 33:47.017
SMOKE WITH ME, BABE
WHAT HAPPENED? YOU CHEAT?

33:47.020 --> 33:49.682
I LIED.

33:49.690 --> 33:50.839
ABOUT WHAT?

33:50.850 --> 33:53.273
AND LAY WITH ME, BABY

33:53.280 --> 33:54.850
I TOLD HER
I STILL LOVED HER.

33:54.860 --> 33:56.600
I JUST WANT
THE SIMPLE THINGS

33:56.610 --> 33:59.522
I JUST WANT YOU
SHE KNEW I WAS LYING.

33:59.530 --> 34:02.033
HOW DO I KNOW YOU WON'T
LIE TO ME, TOO?

34:02.040 --> 34:03.951
MAYBE YOU ALREADY HAVE.

34:03.960 --> 34:05.951
I WANT YOU

34:05.960 --> 34:07.029
YEAH

34:07.040 --> 34:10.203
SO. ..
WHAT ABOUT YOU?

34:10.210 --> 34:11.757
WHAT ARE YOU
ESCAPING FROM?

34:11.760 --> 34:13.330
[ LAUGHS ]

34:13.340 --> 34:16.298
I JUST WANT SOMEONE NOW
TO SMOKE WITH ME, BABY

34:16.300 --> 34:18.040
EVERYTHING.

34:18.050 --> 34:21.133
LAY WITH ME, BABY
MY FAMILY.

34:21.140 --> 34:22.471
LAUGH WITH ME, BABY
MEN.

34:22.480 --> 34:23.936
I DON'T KNOW.

34:23.940 --> 34:25.669
I JUST WANT
THE SIMPLE THINGS

34:25.680 --> 34:29.093
TO SMOKE WITH ME, BABY
ONE DAY,
I JUST STARTED RUNNING.

34:29.100 --> 34:32.183
LAY WITH ME, BABY

34:32.190 --> 34:34.602
LAUGH WITH ME, BABY

34:34.610 --> 34:36.737
WHY DON'T YOU STOP?

34:36.740 --> 34:38.230
I NEVER HAVE.

34:38.240 --> 34:41.994
I JUST WANT YOU

34:42.000 --> 34:43.956
LOOK AT ME, BABY

34:43.960 --> 34:46.997
I JUST WANT YOU

34:47.000 --> 34:48.194
YOU KNOW,
IT'S OKAY TO STOP.

34:48.200 --> 34:49.997
YOU

34:50.000 --> 34:53.788
I WANT YOU, BABY

34:53.800 --> 34:55.756
YOU, ALL RIGHT
I WOULDN'T KNOW HOW.

34:55.760 --> 34:58.661
I JUST WANT YOU

34:58.670 --> 35:00.080
I'LL HELP YOU.

35:00.090 --> 35:01.921
YEAH

35:01.930 --> 35:04.922
SMOKE WITH ME, BABY

35:04.930 --> 35:07.922
LAY WITH ME, BABY, NOW

35:07.930 --> 35:10.558
LAUGH WITH ME, BABY

35:10.560 --> 35:13.893
I JUST WANT
THE SIMPLE THINGS

35:13.900 --> 35:16.357
I JUST WANT YOU

35:16.360 --> 35:18.146
I JUST WANT
THE SIMPLE THINGS

35:24.540 --> 35:26.576
CALEB?

35:29.620 --> 35:32.293
[ HORN HONKS,
ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

35:38.630 --> 35:41.178
OH, DAMN IT!

35:41.180 --> 35:43.216
[ SIREN WAILS IN DISTANCE ]

35:44.970 --> 35:48.053
IT'S PERFECT.

35:48.060 --> 35:50.130
YOU BOOKED IT UNDER THE NAME
I GAVE YOU, RIGHT?

35:50.140 --> 35:52.358
AND WHAT ABOUT THE OTHER STUFF?

35:52.360 --> 35:54.646
NEW I.D., LAPTOP,
ENCRYPTED PHONE.

35:57.730 --> 35:59.220
[ SIGHS ]

36:02.080 --> 36:03.820
I OWE YOU GUYS.

36:03.830 --> 36:06.401
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU, WE DON'T
LET THAT TYPE OF THING GO.

36:06.410 --> 36:08.651
AND THERE ARE
MANY OF US.

36:08.660 --> 36:11.379
IF YOU EVER HAVE TROUBLE
GETTING SOMETHING OR SOMEWHERE,

36:11.380 --> 36:12.745
WE CAN MAKE IT HAPPEN.

36:12.750 --> 36:14.911
[ CHUCKLES ] GOOD.

36:14.920 --> 36:16.740
'CAUSE I MAY
NEED YOUR HELP AGAIN.

36:16.750 --> 36:21.255
WELL, WHO KNOWS?
WE MAY NEED YOURS.

36:22.600 --> 36:24.591
THANK YOU.

36:28.720 --> 36:30.096
[ SIGHS ]

36:32.520 --> 36:34.147
HEY.

36:34.150 --> 36:35.060
HOW WAS YOUR WEEKEND, NIMAH?

36:35.070 --> 36:36.765
VERY GOOD.

36:36.770 --> 36:38.431
I NEED TO STUDY.

36:38.440 --> 36:39.725
HOW ABOUT YOU, PARRISH?

36:39.730 --> 36:40.719
IT WAS FINE.

36:40.730 --> 36:41.617
JUST FINE?

36:41.620 --> 36:43.406
WELL...

36:43.410 --> 36:45.446
I DID MAKE
ONE NEW BUSINESS CONTACT

36:45.450 --> 36:47.520
I WOULDN'T MIND
FOLLOWING UP ON.

36:47.530 --> 36:49.111
OH, I'M SURE
HE'D LIKE THAT.

36:49.120 --> 36:51.532
I'M SURE HE WOULD, TOO.

36:55.590 --> 36:58.241
CALEB. CALEB.

36:58.250 --> 37:01.083
I DON'T KNOW WHAT THE HELL
YOU THOUGHT YOU WERE DOING,

37:01.090 --> 37:03.297
LEAVING ME BEHIND
IN THAT HOTEL ROOM,

37:03.300 --> 37:05.461
BUT I MISSED THE BUS
BACK HERE.

37:05.470 --> 37:07.540
AND IF I GET IN ANY TROUBLE
WHATSOEVER,

37:07.550 --> 37:09.290
I WILL MAKE IT
MY MISSION IN LIFE

37:09.300 --> 37:12.098
TO STRING YOU UP
BY THE SHORT HAIRS.

37:12.770 --> 37:14.431
YOU'RE NOT GONNA APOLOGIZE?

37:14.440 --> 37:16.681
WELL, WE'RE ALL
ON OUR OWN HERE, SISTER.

37:16.690 --> 37:18.601
THAT'S IT?

37:18.610 --> 37:21.818
THAT'S ALL THAT THE IDIOT SAVANT
HAS TO SAY?

37:21.820 --> 37:23.981
YOU, ME, YOUR CAR?

37:23.990 --> 37:25.275
MEET YOU THERE IN 10.

37:29.660 --> 37:31.708
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

37:31.710 --> 37:32.665
KNOCK, KNOCK.

37:34.750 --> 37:36.069
DON'T BOTH ER.

37:36.080 --> 37:37.820
I ALREADY MADE AN APPOINTMENT
WITH MIRANDA'S ASSISTANT.

37:37.830 --> 37:38.990
[ ZIPPER OPENS ]

37:43.840 --> 37:47.298
YOU WERE RIGHT ABOUT ME.

37:47.300 --> 37:49.427
I AM DANGEROUS.

37:49.430 --> 37:50.670
LOOK, NOT NOW, OKAY?

37:50.680 --> 37:53.262
I DON'T HAVE TIME FOR
WHATEVER NEW FICTION

37:53.270 --> 37:55.010
YOU'RE TRYING TO --
PLEASE.

37:58.770 --> 38:00.340
PLEASE.

38:19.330 --> 38:22.049
I WAS IN
THE ISRAELI DEFENSE FORCES.

38:22.050 --> 38:23.870
THEY SENT ME INTO GAZA.

38:23.880 --> 38:26.041
I DIDN'T JUST SEE THINGS.

38:28.720 --> 38:30.620
I DID THINGS.

38:32.980 --> 38:36.768
THINGS THAT HAUNT ME
EVERY SINGLE DAY OF MY LIFE.

38:39.140 --> 38:41.700
AFTER I GOT BACK,
LIVING UNDERCOVER

38:41.700 --> 38:46.694
WAS THE ONLY WAY
THAT I COULD COPE...

38:46.700 --> 38:48.600
WITH WHAT I DID...

38:48.610 --> 38:50.646
WITH MYSELF.

38:50.650 --> 38:53.039
SO I MADE MYSELF A LIE.

38:53.040 --> 38:55.247
I DON'T WEAR GLASSES.

38:57.370 --> 38:59.281
I DON'T EVEN LIKE COFFEE.

38:59.290 --> 39:00.826
[ SIGHS ]

39:00.830 --> 39:04.334
AND I'M NOT...

39:04.340 --> 39:06.831
[Voice breaking ]
I'M -- I'M -- I'M NOT...

39:10.220 --> 39:12.017
[ SNIFFLES ]

39:12.020 --> 39:14.261
I'D UNDERSTAND
IF YOU HATE ME.

39:19.430 --> 39:21.261
YOU SHOULD
KEEP THE GLASSES.

39:25.110 --> 39:26.771
THEY LOOK GOOD ON YOU.

39:26.780 --> 39:28.566
[ LAUGHS ]

39:31.830 --> 39:35.448
SPEAKING PUBLICLY TODAY FOR
THE FIRST TIME, ALEX PARRISH,

39:35.450 --> 39:37.077
THE ACCUSED
GRAND CENTRAL BOMBER,

39:37.080 --> 39:39.116
MADE A PLEA FOR HER INNOCENCE,

39:39.120 --> 39:42.374
LEADING MANY TO QUESTION
WHETHER SHE'S THE REAL BOMBER

39:42.380 --> 39:44.587
OR THE VICTIM OF A COVER-UP.

39:44.590 --> 39:47.457
ALL I CAN DO IS
TELL YOU WHAT HAPPENED.

39:47.460 --> 39:50.088
WHAT HAPPENED TO ME.

39:50.090 --> 39:52.718
I KNOW IT WILL BE HARD
FOR ME TO CONVINCE EVERYONE,

39:52.720 --> 39:54.506
BUT IT'S ALL I HAVE.

39:54.510 --> 39:56.592
OFFICER: Given Charlie's
exemplary behavior,

39:56.600 --> 39:58.716
the board felt he could safely
re-enter the community.

39:58.720 --> 40:01.382
OKAY. [ SIGHS ]

40:01.390 --> 40:03.563
AND WE WILL LEAVE
THE EMPTY CHAIRS
OKAY. THANK YOU.
THANK YOU FOR THE CALL.

40:03.570 --> 40:04.935
TO THOSE WHO SAY
WE CAN'T SIT THERE

40:04.940 --> 40:06.567
I KNOW THAT THERE ARE
PEOPLE OUT THERE,

40:06.570 --> 40:08.185
PEOPLE I CAN COUNT ON.

40:08.190 --> 40:10.567
HEY.
HEY.

40:10.570 --> 40:14.483
UM, WOULD YOU LIKE TO
GO FOR A WALK WITH ME?

40:14.490 --> 40:17.323
NO MISTAKING
WE MAKE OUR BREAKS
YEAH. I'D LOVE THAT.

40:17.330 --> 40:21.289
IF YOU DON'T LIKE OUR 808s,
THEN

40:21.290 --> 40:24.532
PEOPLE WILL SEE ME AS
WHO I AM, AND NOT SOME KILLER,

40:24.540 --> 40:27.498
OR SOME FICTION THAT'S BEEN
CREATED OUT OF THIN AIR.

40:27.500 --> 40:30.378
FIND ME
WHERE THE WILD THINGS ARE

40:30.380 --> 40:34.214
BECAUSE THE ONE THING
I LEARNED AT THE ACADEMY...

40:34.220 --> 40:36.962
IS THAT PEOPLE AREN'T ALWAYS
AS THEY APPEAR.

40:36.970 --> 40:38.255
FIND ME
WHERE THE WILD THINGS ARE
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

40:38.260 --> 40:39.807
DID YOU FIND ANYTHING
ON O'CONNOR?

40:39.810 --> 40:41.937
YES, I DID.
AND YOU NEED TO DROP IT.

40:41.940 --> 40:43.646
WHAT? WHY?

40:43.650 --> 40:45.106
HE TOLD ME EVERYTHING,

40:45.110 --> 40:47.761
AND THOUGH I DON'T AGREE
WITH LIAM'S METHODS,

40:47.770 --> 40:52.616
WHAT HE HIRED YOU FOR IS
A MATTER OF NATIONAL SECURITY.

40:52.620 --> 40:55.612
SOMETIMES, ALL YOU SEE
IS A COVER.

40:55.620 --> 40:59.909
FIND ME
WHERE THE WILD THINGS ARE

40:59.910 --> 41:02.378
SHE KNOWS
WE'RE WORKING WITH ALEX.

41:02.380 --> 41:04.166
OKAY, SO WHEN YOU GOT TO
THE MOSQUE...

41:04.170 --> 41:06.741
ALEX BROKE IN THROUGH
THE SERVICE ENTRANCE.

41:06.750 --> 41:09.071
I ONLY SAW THE HALLWAY
THAT LED INTO THE BASEMENT.

41:09.080 --> 41:11.036
DID SHE TALK TO ANYONE?

41:11.040 --> 41:12.928
JUST THE PEOPLE
FROM THE UNKNOWN.

41:12.930 --> 41:14.579
NO ONE UPSTAIRS
EVEN KNEW THAT WE WERE THERE.

41:14.590 --> 41:16.000
WHAT ABOUT
WHERE SHE WAS HEADED?

41:16.010 --> 41:18.171
DID SHE GIVE
ANY INDICATION?

41:18.180 --> 41:21.138
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

41:21.140 --> 41:23.938
THE CAMERA LIGHT SWITCHED OFF.
EVERYONE STARTED SCRAMBLING.

41:23.940 --> 41:25.180
THAT'S WHEN
YOU WERE KNOCKED OUT.

41:25.190 --> 41:26.646
RIGHT.

41:26.650 --> 41:28.356
WHEN I CAME TO,
AGENT GARDNER AND HIS TEAM

41:28.360 --> 41:30.351
WERE SWEEPING THE ROOM.

41:30.360 --> 41:33.693
OKAY, WELL, I GUESS
THAT IS ALL FOR NOW.

41:41.110 --> 41:44.455
BUT I CHOOSE TO BELIEVE
THAT WHEN THE WORLD SEES ME,

41:44.460 --> 41:48.328
WHEN THEY HEAR ME, THEY'LL
BELIEVE THAT I'M INNOCENT,

41:48.330 --> 41:50.036
BECAUSE I AM.

41:50.040 --> 41:53.259
YOU DIDN'T GIVE US UP.

41:53.260 --> 41:56.332
I HAVE MY ISSUES WITH ALEX,

41:56.340 --> 41:58.217
BUT I DON'T THINK
SHE DID IT.

41:58.220 --> 42:00.461
[ CELLPHONE CHIMES ]

42:00.470 --> 42:01.425
Simon: GOT IT.

42:01.430 --> 42:02.590
IT'S A LIST OF ALL THE AGENTS

42:02.600 --> 42:04.477
WHO WERE AT GRAND CENTRAL
YESTERDAY MORNING.

42:04.480 --> 42:06.550
THE ONLY NAMES I RECOGNIZE
FROM OUR CLASS ARE ME...

42:06.560 --> 42:08.471
ALEX.
AND CALEB HAAS?

42:08.480 --> 42:11.984
WHY WAS HE IN NEW YORK?

42:11.990 --> 42:14.106
THERE'S A REAL TERRORIST
STILL OUT THERE.

42:14.110 --> 42:16.066
AND NO ONE IS LOOKING FOR THEM.

42:16.070 --> 42:18.356
THEY MUST BE FOUND.
